  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Design & Project Coordination Executive",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a motivated and detail-oriented individual to support the <strong>Head of Design</strong> in managing ongoing interior design projects. This role is ideal for someone who is self-driven, eager to learn, and keen to build a long-term career in <strong>high-end interior design project management</strong>.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Assist the Head of Design in coordinating and managing ongoing residential and commercial projects</p></li><li><p>Prepare, update, and track <strong>project progress schedules</strong> and internal reports</p></li><li><p>Handle <strong>ordering, tracking, and coordination of materials, furniture, and goods</strong> with suppliers</p></li><li><p>Support <strong>payment tracking</strong>, including monitoring invoices and project payment milestones</p></li><li><p>Maintain good <strong>client relationships</strong> and support day-to-day project communications</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with designers, suppliers, contractors, and internal teams to ensure smooth project execution</p></li><li><p>Provide general project and administrative support as required</p></li></ul><p>.<strong>Career Development</strong></p><ul><li><p>Hands-on mentorship and guidance from the <strong>Head of Design</strong></p></li><li>Clear career progression path to become a <strong>Project Manager</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Interior Design, Business Management, or related fields</strong></p></li><li><p>Able to <strong>speak and write Chinese</strong> (for client and supplier coordination)</p></li><li><p>Singaporean/Singapore PR only</p></li><li><p><strong>Added advantage</strong> if familiar with design software such as <strong>3ds Max, AutoCAD, SketchUp, or similar tools</strong></p></li><li><p>Prior experience in interior design, construction, or project coordination is an advantage but not mandatory</p></li></ul>",
